                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/1264: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-22T10:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 22, 1938—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 22—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>295. My 294, December 20, 2 p.m. Aranha informs me that he discussed this matter
                    with the President. He added that he had also talked with the Minister of
                    Finance who requested 48 hours for study. He assured me “We will have the whole
                    thing cleaned up by the end of the year.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
